<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60p2/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-24T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 24,
                                        1927—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Your 16, February 21, 4 p.m. Department has no objection to including
                            in Article 16 the last paragraph of Article 7 of draft and the first
                            eleven lines of last paragraph of Article 7 of United States-German
                            Treaty.</p>
                        <p>Please submit proposed text to Department before final agreement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>